  RELEVANCE: Critical for understanding how to specify giving norms in real-world conditions where most affluent people don't donate significantly. Murphy's framework suggests that 10% income pledges might be justified as fair-share contributions even if full compliance would require less from each person. His nonideal theory approach directly addresses the project's concern with implementable norms rather than ideal requirements.

