  RELEVANCE: Represents contemporary development of utilitarian approaches to giving. MacAskill's work raises the question whether giving norms should specify not just how much to give (income vs. assets) but also how effectively (evidence-based charities). His defense of EA against the charge that it's "just utilitarianism" helps clarify the relationship between utilitarian foundations and practical giving guidance.

  POSITION: Effective altruism as a practical movement grounded in but not reducible to utilitarian ethics. Emphasizes evidence-based maximization of impact.
  },
